SUMMARY:The Rise and Fall of the Pennsylvania Railroad Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Did you know the Pennsylvania Railroad—known as “The Pennsy”—was an industry leaderfor 122 years? \n\n\n\nJoin local historian and train enthusiast Jim Bennett for his presentation\, The Rise and Fallof the PA Railroad. This illustrated talk explores how the Pennsylvania Railroad fueledindustry and contributed to the growth and development of York and Lancaster Counties\,becoming the standard by which America’s railroads were measured. \n\n\n\nAttendees will learn about the railroad’s ambitious beginnings\, its rise to prominence\, andthe factors that ultimately led to its decline. Bennett\, a Lancaster County resident\, hasshared his engaging train talks with numerous local groups and brings a passion for railhistory to this in-depth look at one of America’s most influential corporations. \n\n\n\n\n    more info
URL:https://figlancaster.com/event/the-rise-and-fall-of-the-pennsylvania-railroad-lecture/
LOCATION:The Susquehanna National Heritage Area\, 1706 Long Level Road\, Wrightsville\, Pennsylvania\, United States
CATEGORIES:Education & Classes
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://fig.guide/content/uploads/sites/3/2026/03/smoker-lecture-2-scaled.avif
END:VEVENT
