SUMMARY:The World on Edge & Public Disco Porch
DESCRIPTION:Zoetropolis Cinema Stillhouse\, located at 112 N. Water Street in Lancaster\, will host an evening of bold and atmospheric live music on Friday\, April 17\, 2026\, beginning at 8:00 PM\, featuring Harrisburg’s The World on Edge and York ensemble Public Disco Porch.\n\nThe World on Edge is a three-piece cinematic post-rock band from Harrisburg\, PA\, known for widescreen instrumental music built on atmosphere\, tension\, and emotional storytelling. Their sound layers guitars\, dynamic percussion\, and high-fidelity production to create immersive sonic narratives — and audiences can look forward to new material\, with a full-length album due out this summer.\n\nYork’s Public Disco Porch brings a singular vision to the stage: music rooted in the land\, the history\, and the people of South Central Pennsylvania. Their catalog weaves folk-metal riffage\, entrancing percussion\, and muscled low-end into something that feels at once like historical excavation and unhinged spiritual celebration.\n\nTogether\, the two acts offer a rare evening of music that is ambitious\, deeply felt\, and entirely original. \n            \n        \n                \n            \n                \n                \n    Buy Tickets
URL:https://figlancaster.com/event/the-world-on-edge-public-disco-porch/
LOCATION:Zoetropolis Cinema Stillhouse\, 112 North Water Street\, Lancaster\, Pennsylvania\, 17603\, United States
CATEGORIES:Arts & Entertainment
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://fig.guide/content/uploads/sites/3/2026/03/2026-04-Poster-Zoetropolis1-scaled.avif
ORGANIZER;CN="Zoetropolis":MAILTO:info@zoetropolis.com
END:VEVENT
